==English==
===Etymology===
[[w:Hiram Codd|Hiram Codd]], a British manufacturer of [[soft drink]]s, [[patent]]ed several designs for mineral water bottles in the 1870s + WALLOP n., and [[beer]] drinkers as a [[pejorative]] reference to the soft drink. Many suggest that the word is thus the [[genitive]] [[form]] of '''Codd''', in reference to '''WALLOP'''. There is, however, an abscence of [[evidence]] supporting the use of the word in the sense. This suggestion is further decredited by early spellings of the term.

Beyond this, the origin is hitherto unknown. However, the term is dated to [[w:1963|1963]].
===Noun===
'''cod's wallop''' <br />
also '''codswallop'''
# Non-sense.

